<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The new ViewRenderer controller helper is suffering from the same coupling problem some of us had with the Controller initView() method. To utilise a Zend_View subclass we would need to override the entire ViewRenderer::initView method to replace the explicit class name of "Zend_View". Simplicity itself, the solution is to abstract the class name into an option with a default of "Zend_View", say "viewClassName" or similar.</p>

<p>Then I can run off and use "Zps_View" without subclassing.</p>

